(354, '354', 'Banette', 'Ghost', 'https://example.com/images/types/ghost.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/banette.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/banette.mp3', 'BANETTE generates energy for laying\nstrong curses by sticking pins into its\nown body.This POKéMON was originally a pitiful\nplush doll that was thrown away.', 64, 115, 65, 83, 63, 65, 3, 'Shuppet, Banette'),
(355, '355', 'Duskull', 'Ghost', 'https://example.com/images/types/ghost.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/duskull.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/duskull.mp3', 'DUSKULL can pass through any wall no\nmatter how thick it may be.\nOnce this POKéMON chooses a target,it will doggedly pursue the intended\nvictim until the break of dawn.', 20, 40, 90, 30, 90, 25, 3, 'Duskull, Dusclops, Dusknoir'),
(356, '356', 'Dusclops', 'Ghost', 'https://example.com/images/types/ghost.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/dusclops.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/dusclops.mp3', 'DUSCLOPS’s body is completely hollow -\nthere is nothing at all inside.\nIt is said that its body is like a blackhole. This POKéMON will absorb anything\ninto its body, but nothing will ever come\nback out.', 40, 70, 130, 60, 130, 25, 3, 'Duskull, Dusclops, Dusknoir'),
(357, '357', 'Tropius', 'Grass, Flying', 'https://example.com/images/types/grass.png, https://example.com/images/types/flying.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/tropius.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/tropius.mp3', 'The bunches of fruit around TROPIUS’s\nneck are very popular with children.\nThis POKéMON loves fruit, and eats itcontinuously. Apparently, its love for\nfruit resulted in its own outgrowth\nof fruit.', 99, 68, 83, 72, 87, 51, 3, 'Tropius'),
(358, '358', 'Chimecho', 'Psychic', 'https://example.com/images/types/psychic.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/chimecho.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/chimecho.mp3', 'CHIMECHO makes its cries echo\ninside its hollow body. When this\nPOKéMON becomes enraged, its criesresult in ultrasonic waves that have\nthe power to knock foes flying.', 75, 50, 80, 95, 90, 65, 3, 'Chingling, Chimecho'),
(359, '359', 'Absol', 'Dark', 'https://example.com/images/types/dark.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/absol.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/absol.mp3', 'Every time ABSOL appears before people,\nit is followed by a disaster such as an\nearthquake or a tidal wave.As a result, it came to be known as the\ndisaster POKéMON.', 65, 130, 60, 75, 60, 75, 3, 'Absol'),
(360, '360', 'Wynaut', 'Psychic', 'https://example.com/images/types/psychic.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/wynaut.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/wynaut.mp3', 'WYNAUT can always be seen with a big,\nhappy smile on its face. Look at its tail\nto determine if it is angry.When angered, this POKéMON will be\nslapping the ground with its tail.', 95, 23, 48, 23, 48, 23, 3, 'Wynaut, Wobbuffet'),
(361, '361', 'Snorunt', 'Ice', 'https://example.com/images/types/ice.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/snorunt.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/snorunt.mp3', 'SNORUNT live in regions with heavy\nsnowfall. In seasons without snow, such\nas spring and summer, this POKéMONsteals away to live quietly among\nstalactites and stalagmites deep in\ncaverns.', 50, 50, 50, 50, 50, 50, 3, 'Snorunt, Glalie'),
(362, '362', 'Glalie', 'Ice', 'https://example.com/images/types/ice.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/glalie.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/glalie.mp3', 'GLALIE has a body made of rock, which it\nhardens with an armor of ice.\nThis POKéMON has the ability to freezemoisture in the atmosphere into any\nshape it desires.', 80, 80, 80, 80, 80, 80, 3, 'Snorunt, Glalie'),
(363, '363', 'Spheal', 'Ice, Water', 'https://example.com/images/types/ice.png, https://example.com/images/types/water.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/spheal.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/spheal.mp3', 'SPHEAL is much faster rolling than \nwalking to get around. When groups of\nthis POKéMON eat, they all clap at onceto show their pleasure. Because of this,\ntheir mealtimes are noisy.', 70, 40, 50, 55, 50, 25, 3, 'Spheal, Sealeo, Walrein'),
(364, '364', 'Sealeo', 'Ice, Water', 'https://example.com/images/types/ice.png, https://example.com/images/types/water.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/sealeo.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/sealeo.mp3', 'SEALEO has the habit of always juggling\non the tip of its nose anything it sees\nfor the first time.This POKéMON occasionally entertains\nitself by balancing and rolling a SPHEAL\non its nose.', 90, 60, 70, 75, 70, 45, 3, 'Spheal, Sealeo, Walrein'),
(365, '365', 'Walrein', 'Ice, Water', 'https://example.com/images/types/ice.png, https://example.com/images/types/water.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/walrein.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/walrein.mp3', 'It swims through icy seas while shattering\nice floes with its large tusks. It is\nprotected by its thick blubber.', 110, 80, 90, 95, 90, 65, 3, 'Spheal, Sealeo, Walrein'),
(366, '366', 'Clamperl', 'Water', 'https://example.com/images/types/water.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/clamperl.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/clamperl.mp3', 'CLAMPERL’s sturdy shell is not only good\nfor protection - it is also used for\nclamping and catching prey.A fully grown CLAMPERL’s shell will be\nscored with nicks and scratches all\nover.', 35, 64, 85, 74, 55, 32, 3, 'Clamperl, Huntail'),
(367, '367', 'Huntail', 'Water', 'https://example.com/images/types/water.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/huntail.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/huntail.mp3', 'HUNTAIL’s presence went unnoticed by\npeople for a long time because it lives\nat extreme depths in the sea.This POKéMON’s eyes can see clearly\neven in the murky dark depths of the\nocean.', 55, 104, 105, 94, 75, 52, 3, 'Clamperl, Huntail'),
(368, '368', 'Gorebyss', 'Water', 'https://example.com/images/types/water.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/gorebyss.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/gorebyss.mp3', 'GOREBYSS lives in the southern seas\nat extreme depths. Its body is built to\nwithstand the enormous pressure ofwater at incredible depths. Because of\nthis, this POKéMON’s body is unharmed\nby ordinary attacks.', 55, 84, 105, 114, 75, 52, 3, 'Clamperl, Huntail'),
(369, '369', 'Relicanth', 'Water, Rock', 'https://example.com/images/types/water.png, https://example.com/images/types/rock.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/relicanth.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/relicanth.mp3', 'RELICANTH is a POKéMON species that\nexisted for a hundred million years\nwithout ever changing its form.This ancient POKéMON feeds on\nmicroscopic organisms with its\ntoothless mouth.', 100, 90, 130, 45, 65, 55, 3, 'Relicanth'),
(370, '370', 'Luvdisc', 'Water', 'https://example.com/images/types/water.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/luvdisc.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/luvdisc.mp3', 'LUVDISC live in shallow seas in the\ntropics. This heart-shaped POKéMON\nearned its name by swimming afterloving couples it spotted in the\nocean’s waves.', 43, 30, 55, 40, 65, 97, 3, 'Luvdisc'),
(371, '371', 'Bagon', 'Dragon', 'https://example.com/images/types/dragon.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/bagon.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/bagon.mp3', 'Dreaming of one day flying, it practices by leaping\noff cliffs every day.', 45, 75, 60, 40, 30, 50, 3, 'Bagon, Shelgon, Salamence');
INSERT INTO `pokemon` (`id`, `pokedexNumber`, `name`, `type`, `type_images`, `image`, `cri`, `description`, `hp`, `attack`, `defense`, `special_attack`, `special_defense`, `speed`, `gen`, `evolution_chain`) VALUES
(372, '372', 'Shelgon', 'Dragon', 'https://example.com/images/types/dragon.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/shelgon.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/shelgon.mp3', 'Inside SHELGON’s armor-like shell, cells\nare in the midst of transformation\nto create an entirely new body.This POKéMON’s shell is extremely heavy,\nmaking its movements sluggish.', 65, 95, 100, 60, 50, 50, 3, 'Bagon, Shelgon, Salamence'),
(373, '373', 'Salamence', 'Dragon, Flying', 'https://example.com/images/types/dragon.png, https://example.com/images/types/flying.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/salamence.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/salamence.mp3', 'SALAMENCE came about as a result of a\nstrong, long-held dream of growing\nwings. It is said that this powerfuldesire triggered a sudden mutation in\nthis POKéMON’s cells, causing it to\nsprout its magnificent wings.', 95, 135, 80, 110, 80, 100, 3, 'Bagon, Shelgon, Salamence'),
(374, '374', 'Beldum', 'Steel, Psychic', 'https://example.com/images/types/steel.png, https://example.com/images/types/psychic.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/beldum.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/beldum.mp3', 'Instead of blood, a powerful magnetic\nforce courses throughout BELDUM’s\nbody. This POKéMON communicates withothers by sending controlled pulses of\nmagnetism.', 40, 55, 80, 35, 60, 30, 3, 'Beldum, Metang, Metagross'),
(375, '375', 'Metang', 'Steel, Psychic', 'https://example.com/images/types/steel.png, https://example.com/images/types/psychic.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/metang.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/metang.mp3', 'When two BELDUM fuse together, METANG\nis formed. The brains of the BELDUM are\njoined by a magnetic nervous system.By linking its brains magnetically,\nthis POKéMON generates strong\npsychokinetic power.', 60, 75, 100, 55, 80, 50, 3, 'Beldum, Metang, Metagross'),
(376, '376', 'Metagross', 'Steel, Psychic', 'https://example.com/images/types/steel.png, https://example.com/images/types/psychic.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/metagross.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/metagross.mp3', 'METAGROSS has four brains in total.\nCombined, the four brains can breeze\nthrough difficult calculations fasterthan a supercomputer.\nThis POKéMON can float in the air by\ntucking in its four legs.', 80, 135, 130, 95, 90, 70, 3, 'Beldum, Metang, Metagross'),
(377, '377', 'Regirock', 'Rock', 'https://example.com/images/types/rock.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/regirock.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/regirock.mp3', 'Its entire body is made of rock.\nIf any part chips off in battle, it\nattaches rocks to repair itself.', 80, 100, 200, 50, 100, 50, 3, 'Regirock'),
(378, '378', 'Regice', 'Ice', 'https://example.com/images/types/ice.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/regice.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/regice.mp3', 'REGICE’s body was made during an ice\nage. The deep-frozen body can’t be\nmelted, even by fire.This POKéMON controls frigid air of\nminus 328 degrees F.', 80, 50, 100, 100, 200, 50, 3, 'Regice'),
(379, '379', 'Registeel', 'Steel', 'https://example.com/images/types/steel.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/registeel.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/registeel.mp3', 'REGISTEEL has a body that is harder\nthan any kind of metal.\nIts body is apparently hollow.No one has any idea what this POKéMON\neats.', 80, 75, 150, 75, 150, 50, 3, 'Registeel'),
(380, '380', 'Latias', 'Dragon, Psychic', 'https://example.com/images/types/dragon.png, https://example.com/images/types/psychic.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/latias.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/latias.mp3', 'LATIAS is highly sensitive to the\nemotions of people. If it senses any\nhostility, this POKéMON ruffles thefeathers all over its body and cries\nshrilly to intimidate the foe.', 80, 80, 90, 110, 130, 110, 3, 'Latias'),
(381, '381', 'Latios', 'Dragon, Psychic', 'https://example.com/images/types/dragon.png, https://example.com/images/types/psychic.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/latios.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/latios.mp3', 'LATIOS has the ability to make its foe\nsee an image of what it has seen or\nimagines in its head.This POKéMON is intelligent and\nunderstands human speech.', 80, 90, 80, 130, 110, 110, 3, 'Latios'),
(382, '382', 'Kyogre', 'Water', 'https://example.com/images/types/water.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/kyogre.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/kyogre.mp3', 'KYOGRE has the power to create massive\nrain clouds that cover the entire sky\nand bring about torrential downpours.This POKéMON saved people who were\nsuffering from droughts.', 100, 100, 90, 150, 140, 90, 3, 'Kyogre'),
(383, '383', 'Groudon', 'Ground', 'https://example.com/images/types/ground.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/groudon.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/groudon.mp3', 'GROUDON has long been described in \nmythology as the POKéMON that raised\nlands and expanded continents.This POKéMON took to sleep after a\ncataclysmic battle with KYOGRE.', 100, 150, 140, 100, 90, 90, 3, 'Groudon'),
(384, '384', 'Rayquaza', 'Dragon, Flying', 'https://example.com/images/types/dragon.png, https://example.com/images/types/flying.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/rayquaza.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/rayquaza.mp3', 'RAYQUAZA lived for hundreds of millions\nof years in the earth’s ozone layer, \nnever descending to the ground.This POKéMON appears to feed on water\nand particles in the atmosphere.', 105, 150, 90, 150, 90, 95, 3, 'Rayquaza'),
(385, '385', 'Jirachi', 'Steel, Psychic', 'https://example.com/images/types/steel.png, https://example.com/images/types/psychic.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/jirachi.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/jirachi.mp3', 'A legend states that JIRACHI will make\ntrue any wish that is written on notes\nattached to its head when it awakens.If this POKéMON senses danger, it will\nfight without awakening.', 100, 100, 100, 100, 100, 100, 3, 'Jirachi'),
(386, '386', 'Deoxysnormal', 'Psychic', 'https://example.com/images/types/psychic.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/deoxys.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/deoxys.mp3', 'The DNA of a space virus underwent a\nsudden mutation upon exposure to a\nlaser beam and resulted in DEOXYS.The crystalline organ on this POKéMON’s\nchest appears to be its brain.', 50, 150, 50, 150, 50, 150, 3, 'Deoxys'),
(387, '387', 'Turtwig', 'Grass', 'https://example.com/images/types/grass.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/turtwig.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/turtwig.mp3', 'Made from soil, the shell on its\nback hardens when it drinks water.\nIt lives along lakes.', 55, 68, 64, 45, 55, 31, 4, 'Turtwig, Grotle, Torterra'),
(388, '388', 'Grotle', 'Grass', 'https://example.com/images/types/grass.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/grotle.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/grotle.mp3', 'It knows where pure water wells\nup. It carries fellow Pokémon there\non its back.', 75, 89, 85, 55, 65, 36, 4, 'Turtwig, Grotle, Torterra'),
(389, '389', 'Torterra', 'Grass, Ground', 'https://example.com/images/types/grass.png, https://example.com/images/types/ground.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/torterra.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/torterra.mp3', 'Small Pokémon occasionally gather\non its unmoving back to begin\nbuilding their nests.', 95, 109, 105, 75, 85, 56, 4, 'Turtwig, Grotle, Torterra'),
(390, '390', 'Chimchar', 'Fire', 'https://example.com/images/types/fire.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/chimchar.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/chimchar.mp3', 'It agilely scales sheer cliffs to\nlive atop craggy mountains. Its\nfire is put out when it sleeps.', 44, 58, 44, 58, 44, 61, 4, 'Chimchar, Monferno, Infernape'),
(391, '391', 'Monferno', 'Fire, Fighting', 'https://example.com/images/types/fire.png, https://example.com/images/types/fighting.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/monferno.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/monferno.mp3', 'To intimidate attackers, it\nstretches the fire on its tail\nto make itself appear bigger.', 64, 78, 52, 78, 52, 81, 4, 'Chimchar, Monferno, Infernape'),
(392, '392', 'Infernape', 'Fire, Fighting', 'https://example.com/images/types/fire.png, https://example.com/images/types/fighting.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/infernape.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/infernape.mp3', 'It uses a special kind of martial\narts involving all its limbs.\nIts fire never goes out.', 76, 104, 71, 104, 71, 108, 4, 'Chimchar, Monferno, Infernape'),
(393, '393', 'Piplup', 'Water', 'https://example.com/images/types/water.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/piplup.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/piplup.mp3', 'Because it is very proud, it hates\naccepting food from people. Its\nthick down guards it from cold.', 53, 51, 53, 61, 56, 40, 4, 'Piplup, Prinplup, Empoleon'),
(394, '394', 'Prinplup', 'Water', 'https://example.com/images/types/water.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/prinplup.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/prinplup.mp3', 'It lives alone, away from others.\nApparently, every one of them\nbelieves it is the most important.', 64, 66, 68, 81, 76, 50, 4, 'Piplup, Prinplup, Empoleon'),
(395, '395', 'Empoleon', 'Water, Steel', 'https://example.com/images/types/water.png, https://example.com/images/types/steel.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/empoleon.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/empoleon.mp3', 'The three horns that extend from\nits beak attest to its power. The\nleader has the biggest horns.', 84, 86, 88, 111, 101, 60, 4, 'Piplup, Prinplup, Empoleon'),
(396, '396', 'Starly', 'Normal, Flying', 'https://example.com/images/types/normal.png, https://example.com/images/types/flying.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/starly.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/starly.mp3', 'They flock in great numbers.\nThough small, they flap their\nwings with great power.', 40, 55, 30, 30, 30, 60, 4, 'Starly, Staravia, Staraptor'),
(397, '397', 'Staravia', 'Normal, Flying', 'https://example.com/images/types/normal.png, https://example.com/images/types/flying.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/staravia.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/staravia.mp3', 'It flies around forests and fields\nin search of bug Pokémon.\nIt stays within a huge flock.', 55, 75, 50, 40, 40, 80, 4, 'Starly, Staravia, Staraptor'),
(398, '398', 'Staraptor', 'Normal, Flying', 'https://example.com/images/types/normal.png, https://example.com/images/types/flying.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/staraptor.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/staraptor.mp3', 'It has a savage nature. It will\ncourageously challenge foes that\nare much larger.', 85, 120, 70, 50, 60, 100, 4, 'Starly, Staravia, Staraptor'),
(399, '399', 'Bidoof', 'Normal', 'https://example.com/images/types/normal.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/bidoof.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/bidoof.mp3', 'With nerves of steel, nothing can\nperturb it. It is more agile and\nactive than it appears.', 59, 45, 40, 35, 40, 31, 4, 'Bidoof, Bibarel'),
(400, '400', 'Bibarel', 'Normal, Water', 'https://example.com/images/types/normal.png, https://example.com/images/types/water.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/bibarel.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/bibarel.mp3', 'It makes its nest by damming\nstreams with bark and mud. It is\nknown as an industrious worker.', 79, 85, 60, 55, 60, 71, 4, 'Bidoof, Bibarel'),
(401, '401', 'Kricketot', 'Bug', 'https://example.com/images/types/bug.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/kricketot.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/kricketot.mp3', 'It shakes its head back to front,\ncausing its antennae to hit each\nother and sound like a xylophone.', 37, 25, 41, 25, 41, 25, 4, 'Kricketot, Kricketune'),
(402, '402', 'Kricketune', 'Bug', 'https://example.com/images/types/bug.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/kricketune.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/kricketune.mp3', 'It crosses its knifelike arms in\nfront of its chest when it cries.\nIt can compose melodies ad lib.', 77, 85, 51, 55, 51, 65, 4, 'Kricketot, Kricketune'),
(403, '403', 'Shinx', 'Electric', 'https://example.com/images/types/electric.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/shinx.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/shinx.mp3', 'All of its fur dazzles if danger is\nsensed. It flees while the foe is\nmomentarily blinded.', 45, 65, 34, 40, 34, 45, 4, 'Shinx, Luxio, Luxray'),
