(730, '730', 'Primarina', 'Water, Fairy', 'https://example.com/images/types/water.png, https://example.com/images/types/fairy.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/primarina.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/primarina.mp3', 'It controls its water balloons with song. The\nmelody is learned from others of its kind and is\npassed down from one generation to the next.', 80, 74, 74, 126, 116, 60, 7, 'Popplio, Brionne, Primarina'),
(731, '731', 'Pikipek', 'Normal, Flying', 'https://example.com/images/types/normal.png, https://example.com/images/types/flying.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/pikipek.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/pikipek.mp3', 'It can peck at a rate of 16 times a second to\ndrill holes in trees. It uses the holes for food\nstorage and for nesting.', 35, 75, 30, 30, 30, 65, 7, 'Pikipek, Trumbeak, Toucannon'),
(732, '732', 'Trumbeak', 'Normal, Flying', 'https://example.com/images/types/normal.png, https://example.com/images/types/flying.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/trumbeak.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/trumbeak.mp3', 'It eats berries and stores their seeds in its\nbeak. When it encounters enemies or prey,\nit fires off all the seeds in a burst.', 55, 85, 50, 40, 50, 75, 7, 'Pikipek, Trumbeak, Toucannon'),
(733, '733', 'Toucannon', 'Normal, Flying', 'https://example.com/images/types/normal.png, https://example.com/images/types/flying.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/toucannon.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/toucannon.mp3', 'When it battles, its beak heats up. The\ntemperature can easily exceed 212 degrees\nFahrenheit, causing severe burns when it hits.', 80, 120, 75, 75, 75, 60, 7, 'Pikipek, Trumbeak, Toucannon'),
(734, '734', 'Yungoos', 'Normal', 'https://example.com/images/types/normal.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/yungoos.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/yungoos.mp3', 'With its sharp fangs, it will bite anything.\nIt did not originally live in Alola but was\nimported from another region.', 48, 70, 30, 30, 30, 45, 7, 'Yungoos, Gumshoos'),
(735, '735', 'Gumshoos', 'Normal', 'https://example.com/images/types/normal.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/gumshoos.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/gumshoos.mp3', 'When it finds a trace of its prey, it patiently\nstakes out the location...but it’s always snoozing\nby nightfall.', 88, 110, 60, 55, 60, 45, 7, 'Yungoos, Gumshoos'),
(736, '736', 'Grubbin', 'Bug', 'https://example.com/images/types/bug.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/grubbin.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/grubbin.mp3', 'Its strong jaw enables it to scrape trees and\nslurp out the sap. It normally lives underground.', 47, 62, 45, 55, 45, 46, 7, 'Grubbin, Charjabug, Vikavolt'),
(737, '737', 'Charjabug', 'Bug, Electric', 'https://example.com/images/types/bug.png, https://example.com/images/types/electric.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/charjabug.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/charjabug.mp3', 'Its body is capable of storing electricity. On\ncamping trips, people are grateful to have\none around.', 57, 82, 95, 55, 75, 36, 7, 'Grubbin, Charjabug, Vikavolt'),
(738, '738', 'Vikavolt', 'Bug, Electric', 'https://example.com/images/types/bug.png, https://example.com/images/types/electric.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/vikavolt.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/vikavolt.mp3', 'It zips around, on sharp lookout for an opening.\nIt concentrates electrical energy within its large\njaws and uses it to zap its enemies.', 77, 70, 90, 145, 75, 43, 7, 'Grubbin, Charjabug, Vikavolt'),
(739, '739', 'Crabrawler', 'Fighting', 'https://example.com/images/types/fighting.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/crabrawler.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/crabrawler.mp3', 'While guarding its weak points with its pincers,\nit looks for an opening and unleashes punches.\nWhen it loses, it foams at the mouth and faints.', 47, 82, 57, 42, 47, 63, 7, 'Crabrawler, Crabominable'),
(740, '740', 'Crabominable', 'Fighting, Ice', 'https://example.com/images/types/fighting.png, https://example.com/images/types/ice.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/crabominable.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/crabominable.mp3', 'It aimed for the top but got lost and ended up\non a snowy mountain. Being forced to endure\nthe cold, this Pokémon evolved and grew fur.', 97, 132, 77, 62, 67, 43, 7, 'Crabrawler, Crabominable'),
(741, '741', 'Oricoriobaile', 'Fire, Flying', 'https://example.com/images/types/fire.png, https://example.com/images/types/flying.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/oricoriobaile.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/oricoriobaile.mp3', 'It beats its wings together to create fire.\nAs it moves in the steps of its beautiful dance,\nit bathes opponents in intense flames.', 75, 70, 70, 98, 70, 93, 7, 'Oricorio'),
(742, '742', 'Cutiefly', 'Bug, Fairy', 'https://example.com/images/types/bug.png, https://example.com/images/types/fairy.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/cutiefly.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/cutiefly.mp3', 'It feeds on the nectar and pollen of flowers.\nBecause it’s able to sense auras, it can identify\nwhich flowers are about to bloom.', 40, 45, 40, 55, 40, 84, 7, 'Cutiefly, Ribombee'),
(743, '743', 'Ribombee', 'Bug, Fairy', 'https://example.com/images/types/bug.png, https://example.com/images/types/fairy.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/ribombee.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/ribombee.mp3', 'It rolls up pollen into puffs. It makes many\ndifferent varieties, some used as food and\nothers used in battle.', 60, 55, 60, 95, 70, 124, 7, 'Cutiefly, Ribombee'),
(744, '744', 'Rockruff', 'Rock', 'https://example.com/images/types/rock.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/rockruff.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/rockruff.mp3', 'It’s considered to be a good Pokémon for\nbeginners because of its friendliness, but its\ndisposition grows rougher as it grows up.', 45, 65, 40, 30, 40, 60, 7, 'Rockruff, Lycanroc'),
(745, '745', 'Lycanrocmidday', 'Rock', 'https://example.com/images/types/rock.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/lycanrocmidday.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/lycanrocmidday.mp3', 'Its quick movements confuse its enemies.\nWell equipped with claws and fangs, it also uses\nthe sharp rocks in its mane as weapons.', 75, 115, 65, 55, 65, 112, 7, 'Rockruff, Lycanroc'),
(746, '746', 'Wishiwashisolo', 'Water', 'https://example.com/images/types/water.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/wishiwashisolo.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/wishiwashisolo.mp3', 'When it’s in trouble, its eyes moisten and begin\nto shine. The shining light attracts its comrades,\nand they stand together against their enemies.', 45, 20, 20, 25, 25, 40, 7, 'Wishiwashi'),
(747, '747', 'Mareanie', 'Poison, Water', 'https://example.com/images/types/poison.png, https://example.com/images/types/water.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/mareanie.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/mareanie.mp3', 'It plunges the poison spike on its head into its\nprey. When the prey has weakened, Mareanie\ndeals the finishing blow with its 10 tentacles.', 50, 53, 62, 43, 52, 45, 7, 'Mareanie, Toxapex'),
(748, '748', 'Toxapex', 'Poison, Water', 'https://example.com/images/types/poison.png, https://example.com/images/types/water.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/toxapex.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/toxapex.mp3', 'Toxapex crawls along the ocean floor on its\n12 legs. It leaves a trail of Corsola bits\nscattered in its wake.', 50, 63, 152, 53, 142, 35, 7, 'Mareanie, Toxapex'),
(749, '749', 'Mudbray', 'Ground', 'https://example.com/images/types/ground.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/mudbray.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/mudbray.mp3', 'The mud stuck to Mudbray’s hooves enhances\nits grip and its powerful running gait.', 70, 100, 70, 45, 55, 45, 7, 'Mudbray, Mudsdale'),
(750, '750', 'Mudsdale', 'Ground', 'https://example.com/images/types/ground.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/mudsdale.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/mudsdale.mp3', 'It spits a mud that provides resistance to both\nwind and rain, so the walls of old houses were\noften coated with it.', 100, 125, 100, 55, 85, 35, 7, 'Mudbray, Mudsdale'),
(751, '751', 'Dewpider', 'Water, Bug', 'https://example.com/images/types/water.png, https://example.com/images/types/bug.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/dewpider.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/dewpider.mp3', 'It crawls onto the land in search of food.\nIts water bubble allows it to breathe and\nprotects its soft head.', 38, 40, 52, 40, 72, 27, 7, 'Dewpider, Araquanid'),
(752, '752', 'Araquanid', 'Water, Bug', 'https://example.com/images/types/water.png, https://example.com/images/types/bug.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/araquanid.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/araquanid.mp3', 'It delivers headbutts with the water bubble\non its head. Small Pokémon get sucked into\nthe bubble, where they drown.', 68, 70, 92, 50, 132, 42, 7, 'Dewpider, Araquanid');
INSERT INTO `pokemon` (`id`, `pokedexNumber`, `name`, `type`, `type_images`, `image`, `cri`, `description`, `hp`, `attack`, `defense`, `special_attack`, `special_defense`, `speed`, `gen`, `evolution_chain`) VALUES
(753, '753', 'Fomantis', 'Grass', 'https://example.com/images/types/grass.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/fomantis.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/fomantis.mp3', 'During the day, it sleeps and soaks up light.\nWhen night falls, it walks around looking\nfor a safer place to sleep.', 40, 55, 35, 50, 35, 35, 7, 'Fomantis, Lurantis'),
(754, '754', 'Lurantis', 'Grass', 'https://example.com/images/types/grass.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/lurantis.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/lurantis.mp3', 'It requires a lot of effort to maintain Lurantis’s\nvivid coloring, but some collectors enjoy this\nwork and treat it as their hobby.', 70, 105, 90, 80, 90, 45, 7, 'Fomantis, Lurantis'),
(755, '755', 'Morelull', 'Grass, Fairy', 'https://example.com/images/types/grass.png, https://example.com/images/types/fairy.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/morelull.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/morelull.mp3', 'It scatters spores that flicker and glow. Anyone\nseeing these lights falls into a deep slumber.', 40, 35, 55, 65, 75, 15, 7, 'Morelull, Shiinotic'),
(756, '756', 'Shiinotic', 'Grass, Fairy', 'https://example.com/images/types/grass.png, https://example.com/images/types/fairy.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/shiinotic.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/shiinotic.mp3', 'Forests where Shiinotic live are treacherous to\nenter at night. People confused by its strange\nlights can never find their way home again.', 60, 45, 80, 90, 100, 30, 7, 'Morelull, Shiinotic'),
(757, '757', 'Salandit', 'Poison, Fire', 'https://example.com/images/types/poison.png, https://example.com/images/types/fire.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/salandit.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/salandit.mp3', 'It burns its bodily fluids to create a poisonous\ngas. When its enemies become disoriented from\ninhaling the gas, it attacks them.', 48, 44, 40, 71, 40, 77, 7, 'Salandit, Salazzle'),
(758, '758', 'Salazzle', 'Poison, Fire', 'https://example.com/images/types/poison.png, https://example.com/images/types/fire.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/salazzle.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/salazzle.mp3', 'For some reason, only females have been found.\nIt creates a reverse harem of male Salandit that\nit lives with.', 68, 64, 60, 111, 60, 117, 7, 'Salandit, Salazzle'),
(759, '759', 'Stufful', 'Normal, Fighting', 'https://example.com/images/types/normal.png, https://example.com/images/types/fighting.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/stufful.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/stufful.mp3', 'Despite its adorable appearance, when it gets\nangry and flails about, its arms and legs could\nknock a pro wrestler sprawling.', 70, 75, 50, 45, 50, 50, 7, 'Stufful, Bewear'),
(760, '760', 'Bewear', 'Normal, Fighting', 'https://example.com/images/types/normal.png, https://example.com/images/types/fighting.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/bewear.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/bewear.mp3', 'This immensely dangerous Pokémon\npossesses overwhelming physical strength.\nIts habitat is generally off-limits.', 120, 125, 80, 55, 60, 60, 7, 'Stufful, Bewear'),
(761, '761', 'Bounsweet', 'Grass', 'https://example.com/images/types/grass.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/bounsweet.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/bounsweet.mp3', 'A delectable aroma pours from its body.\nThey are often swallowed whole by Toucannon\nlured by that wafting deliciousness.', 42, 30, 38, 30, 38, 32, 7, 'Bounsweet, Steenee, Tsareena'),
(762, '762', 'Steenee', 'Grass', 'https://example.com/images/types/grass.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/steenee.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/steenee.mp3', 'The sepals on its head developed to protect its\nbody. These are quite hard, so even if pecked\nby bird Pokémon, this Pokémon is totally fine.', 52, 40, 48, 40, 48, 62, 7, 'Bounsweet, Steenee, Tsareena'),
(763, '763', 'Tsareena', 'Grass', 'https://example.com/images/types/grass.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/tsareena.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/tsareena.mp3', 'Its long, striking legs aren’t just for show but to\nbe used to kick with skill. In victory, it shows off\nby kicking the defeated, laughing boisterously.', 72, 120, 98, 50, 98, 72, 7, 'Bounsweet, Steenee, Tsareena'),
(764, '764', 'Comfey', 'Fairy', 'https://example.com/images/types/fairy.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/comfey.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/comfey.mp3', 'It attaches flowers to its highly nutritious vine.\nThis revitalizes the flowers, and they give off\nan aromatic scent.', 51, 52, 90, 82, 110, 100, 7, 'Comfey'),
(765, '765', 'Oranguru', 'Normal, Psychic', 'https://example.com/images/types/normal.png, https://example.com/images/types/psychic.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/oranguru.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/oranguru.mp3', 'Known for its extreme intelligence, this Pokémon\nwill look down on inexperienced Trainers, so it’s\nbest suited to veteran Trainers.', 90, 60, 80, 90, 110, 60, 7, 'Oranguru'),
(766, '766', 'Passimian', 'Fighting', 'https://example.com/images/types/fighting.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/passimian.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/passimian.mp3', 'They form groups of roughly 20 individuals.\nTheir mutual bond is remarkable—they will never\nlet down a comrade.', 100, 120, 90, 40, 60, 80, 7, 'Passimian'),
(767, '767', 'Wimpod', 'Bug, Water', 'https://example.com/images/types/bug.png, https://example.com/images/types/water.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/wimpod.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/wimpod.mp3', 'This Pokémon is a coward. As it desperately\ndashes off, the flailing of its many legs leaves a\nsparkling clean path in its wake.', 25, 35, 40, 20, 30, 80, 7, 'Wimpod, Golisopod'),
(768, '768', 'Golisopod', 'Bug, Water', 'https://example.com/images/types/bug.png, https://example.com/images/types/water.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/golisopod.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/golisopod.mp3', 'With a flashing slash of its giant sharp claws,\nit cleaves seawater—or even air—right in two.', 75, 125, 140, 60, 90, 40, 7, 'Wimpod, Golisopod'),
(769, '769', 'Sandygast', 'Ghost, Ground', 'https://example.com/images/types/ghost.png, https://example.com/images/types/ground.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/sandygast.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/sandygast.mp3', 'Born from a sand mound playfully built by a\nchild, this Pokémon embodies the grudges of\nthe departed.', 55, 55, 80, 70, 45, 15, 7, 'Sandygast, Palossand'),
(770, '770', 'Palossand', 'Ghost, Ground', 'https://example.com/images/types/ghost.png, https://example.com/images/types/ground.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/palossand.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/palossand.mp3', 'Possessed people controlled by this Pokémon\ntransformed its sand mound into a castle. As it\nevolved, its power to curse grew ever stronger.', 85, 75, 110, 100, 75, 35, 7, 'Sandygast, Palossand'),
(771, '771', 'Pyukumuku', 'Water', 'https://example.com/images/types/water.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/pyukumuku.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/pyukumuku.mp3', 'It’s covered in a slime that keeps its skin moist,\nallowing it to stay on land for days without\ndrying up.', 55, 60, 130, 30, 130, 5, 7, 'Pyukumuku'),
(772, '772', 'Typenull', 'Normal', 'https://example.com/images/types/normal.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/typenull.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/typenull.mp3', 'The heavy control mask it wears suppresses its\nintrinsic capabilities. This Pokémon has some\nhidden special power.', 95, 95, 95, 95, 95, 59, 7, 'Type-null, Silvally'),
(773, '773', 'Silvally', 'Normal', 'https://example.com/images/types/normal.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/silvally.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/silvally.mp3', 'Its trust in its partner is what awakens it.\nThis Pokémon is capable of changing its type,\na flexibility that is well displayed in battle.', 95, 95, 95, 95, 95, 95, 7, 'Type-null, Silvally'),
(774, '774', 'Miniorredmeteor', 'Rock, Flying', 'https://example.com/images/types/rock.png, https://example.com/images/types/flying.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/miniorredmeteor.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/miniorredmeteor.mp3', 'Originally making its home in the ozone layer,\nit hurtles to the ground when the shell enclosing\nits body grows too heavy.', 60, 60, 100, 60, 100, 60, 7, 'Minior'),
(775, '775', 'Komala', 'Normal', 'https://example.com/images/types/normal.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/komala.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/komala.mp3', 'It is born asleep, and it dies asleep. All its\nmovements are apparently no more than the\nresults of it tossing and turning in its dreams.', 65, 115, 65, 75, 95, 65, 7, 'Komala'),
(776, '776', 'Turtonator', 'Fire, Dragon', 'https://example.com/images/types/fire.png, https://example.com/images/types/dragon.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/turtonator.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/turtonator.mp3', 'The shell on its back is chemically unstable\nand explodes violently if struck. The hole in its\nstomach is its weak point.', 60, 78, 135, 91, 85, 36, 7, 'Turtonator'),
(777, '777', 'Togedemaru', 'Electric, Steel', 'https://example.com/images/types/electric.png, https://example.com/images/types/steel.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/togedemaru.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/togedemaru.mp3', 'The spiny fur on its back is normally at rest.\nWhen this Pokémon becomes agitated, its fur\nstands on end and stabs into its attackers.', 65, 98, 63, 40, 73, 96, 7, 'Togedemaru'),
(778, '778', 'Mimikyudisguised', 'Ghost, Fairy', 'https://example.com/images/types/ghost.png, https://example.com/images/types/fairy.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/mimikyudisguised.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/mimikyudisguised.mp3', 'Its actual appearance is unknown. A scholar\nwho saw what was under its rag was\noverwhelmed by terror and died from the shock.', 55, 90, 80, 50, 105, 96, 7, 'Mimikyu'),
(779, '779', 'Bruxish', 'Water, Psychic', 'https://example.com/images/types/water.png, https://example.com/images/types/psychic.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/bruxish.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/bruxish.mp3', 'When it unleashes its psychic power from the\nprotuberance on its head, the grating sound\nof grinding teeth echoes through the area.', 68, 105, 70, 70, 70, 92, 7, 'Bruxish'),
(780, '780', 'Drampa', 'Normal, Dragon', 'https://example.com/images/types/normal.png, https://example.com/images/types/dragon.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/drampa.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/drampa.mp3', 'It has a compassionate personality, but if it is\nangered, it completely destroys its surroundings\nwith its intense breath.', 78, 60, 85, 135, 91, 36, 7, 'Drampa'),
(781, '781', 'Dhelmise', 'Ghost, Grass', 'https://example.com/images/types/ghost.png, https://example.com/images/types/grass.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/dhelmise.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/dhelmise.mp3', 'Swinging its massive anchor, it can KO Wailord\nin a single blow. What appears to be green\nseaweed is actually its body.', 70, 131, 100, 86, 90, 40, 7, 'Dhelmise'),
(782, '782', 'Jangmoo', 'Dragon', 'https://example.com/images/types/dragon.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/jangmoo.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/jangmoo.mp3', 'It expresses its feelings by smacking\nits scales. Metallic sounds echo through\nthe tall mountains where Jangmo-o lives.', 45, 55, 65, 45, 45, 45, 7, 'Jangmo-o, Hakamo-o, Kommo-o'),
(783, '783', 'Hakamoo', 'Dragon, Fighting', 'https://example.com/images/types/dragon.png, https://example.com/images/types/fighting.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/hakamoo.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/hakamoo.mp3', 'It leaps at its prey with a courageous shout.\nIts scaly punches tear its opponents to shreds.', 55, 75, 90, 65, 70, 65, 7, 'Jangmo-o, Hakamo-o, Kommo-o'),
