(835, '835', 'Yamper', 'Electric', 'https://example.com/images/types/electric.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/yamper.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/yamper.mp3', 'This Pokémon is very popular as a herding dog\nin the Galar region. As it runs, it generates\nelectricity from the base of its tail.', 59, 45, 50, 40, 50, 26, 8, 'Yamper, Boltund'),
(836, '836', 'Boltund', 'Electric', 'https://example.com/images/types/electric.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/boltund.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/boltund.mp3', 'This Pokémon generates electricity and channels\nit into its legs to keep them going strong.\nBoltund can run nonstop for three full days.', 69, 90, 60, 90, 60, 121, 8, 'Yamper, Boltund'),
(837, '837', 'Rolycoly', 'Rock', 'https://example.com/images/types/rock.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/rolycoly.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/rolycoly.mp3', 'Most of its body has the same composition as\ncoal. Fittingly, this Pokémon was first discovered\nin coal mines about 400 years ago.', 30, 40, 50, 40, 50, 30, 8, 'Rolycoly, Carkol, Coalossal'),
(838, '838', 'Carkol', 'Rock, Fire', 'https://example.com/images/types/rock.png, https://example.com/images/types/fire.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/carkol.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/carkol.mp3', 'It forms coal inside its body. Coal dropped by\nthis Pokémon once helped fuel the lives of\npeople in the Galar region.', 80, 60, 90, 60, 70, 50, 8, 'Rolycoly, Carkol, Coalossal'),
(839, '839', 'Coalossal', 'Rock, Fire', 'https://example.com/images/types/rock.png, https://example.com/images/types/fire.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/coalossal.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/coalossal.mp3', 'It’s usually peaceful, but the vandalism of mines\nenrages it. Offenders will be incinerated with\nflames that reach 2,700 degrees Fahrenheit.', 110, 80, 120, 80, 90, 30, 8, 'Rolycoly, Carkol, Coalossal'),
(840, '840', 'Applin', 'Grass, Dragon', 'https://example.com/images/types/grass.png, https://example.com/images/types/dragon.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/applin.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/applin.mp3', 'It spends its entire life inside an apple. It hides\nfrom its natural enemies, bird Pokémon, by\npretending it’s just an apple and nothing more.', 40, 40, 80, 40, 40, 20, 8, 'Applin, Flapple'),
(841, '841', 'Flapple', 'Grass, Dragon', 'https://example.com/images/types/grass.png, https://example.com/images/types/dragon.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/flapple.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/flapple.mp3', 'It ate a sour apple, and that induced its\nevolution. In its cheeks, it stores an acid\ncapable of causing chemical burns.', 70, 110, 80, 95, 60, 70, 8, 'Applin, Flapple'),
(842, '842', 'Appletun', 'Grass, Dragon', 'https://example.com/images/types/grass.png, https://example.com/images/types/dragon.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/appletun.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/appletun.mp3', 'Eating a sweet apple caused its evolution.\nA nectarous scent wafts from its body, luring in\nthe bug Pokémon it preys on.', 110, 85, 80, 100, 80, 30, 8, 'Applin, Flapple'),
(843, '843', 'Silicobra', 'Ground', 'https://example.com/images/types/ground.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/silicobra.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/silicobra.mp3', 'As it digs, it swallows sand and stores it in its\nneck pouch. The pouch can hold more than\n17 pounds of sand.', 52, 57, 75, 35, 50, 46, 8, 'Silicobra, Sandaconda'),
(844, '844', 'Sandaconda', 'Ground', 'https://example.com/images/types/ground.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/sandaconda.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/sandaconda.mp3', 'When it contracts its body, over 220 pounds of\nsand sprays from its nose. If it ever runs out of\nsand, it becomes disheartened.', 72, 107, 125, 65, 70, 71, 8, 'Silicobra, Sandaconda'),
(845, '845', 'Cramorant', 'Flying, Water', 'https://example.com/images/types/flying.png, https://example.com/images/types/water.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/cramorant.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/cramorant.mp3', 'It’s so strong that it can knock out some\nopponents in a single hit, but it also may\nforget what it’s battling midfight.', 70, 85, 55, 85, 95, 85, 8, 'Cramorant'),
(846, '846', 'Arrokuda', 'Water', 'https://example.com/images/types/water.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/arrokuda.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/arrokuda.mp3', 'If it sees any movement around it, this Pokémon\ncharges for it straightaway, leading with its\nsharply pointed jaw. It’s very proud of that jaw.', 41, 63, 40, 40, 30, 66, 8, 'Arrokuda, Barraskewda'),
(847, '847', 'Barraskewda', 'Water', 'https://example.com/images/types/water.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/barraskewda.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/barraskewda.mp3', 'This Pokémon has a jaw that’s as sharp as a spear\nand as strong as steel. Apparently Barraskewda’s\nflesh is surprisingly tasty, too.', 61, 123, 60, 60, 50, 136, 8, 'Arrokuda, Barraskewda'),
(848, '848', 'Toxel', 'Electric, Poison', 'https://example.com/images/types/electric.png, https://example.com/images/types/poison.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/toxel.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/toxel.mp3', 'It stores poison in an internal poison sac and\nsecretes that poison through its skin. If you touch\nthis Pokémon, a tingling sensation follows.', 40, 38, 35, 54, 35, 40, 8, 'Toxel, Toxtricity'),
(849, '849', 'Toxtricityamped', 'Electric, Poison', 'https://example.com/images/types/electric.png, https://example.com/images/types/poison.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/toxtricityamped.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/toxtricityamped.mp3', 'When this Pokémon sounds as if it’s strumming a\nguitar, it’s actually clawing at the protrusions on\nits chest to generate electricity.', 75, 98, 70, 114, 70, 75, 8, 'Toxel, Toxtricity'),
(850, '850', 'Sizzlipede', 'Fire, Bug', 'https://example.com/images/types/fire.png, https://example.com/images/types/bug.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/sizzlipede.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/sizzlipede.mp3', 'It stores flammable gas in its body and uses it to\ngenerate heat. The yellow sections on its belly\nget particularly hot.', 50, 65, 45, 50, 50, 45, 8, 'Sizzlipede, Centiskorch'),
(851, '851', 'Centiskorch', 'Fire, Bug', 'https://example.com/images/types/fire.png, https://example.com/images/types/bug.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/centiskorch.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/centiskorch.mp3', 'When it heats up, its body temperature reaches\nabout 1,500 degrees Fahrenheit. It lashes its\nbody like a whip and launches itself at enemies.', 100, 115, 65, 90, 90, 65, 8, 'Sizzlipede, Centiskorch'),
(852, '852', 'Clobbopus', 'Fighting', 'https://example.com/images/types/fighting.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/clobbopus.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/clobbopus.mp3', 'It’s very curious, but its means of investigating\nthings is to try to punch them with its tentacles.\nThe search for food is what brings it onto land.', 50, 68, 60, 50, 50, 32, 8, 'Clobbopus, Grapploct'),
(853, '853', 'Grapploct', 'Fighting', 'https://example.com/images/types/fighting.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/grapploct.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/grapploct.mp3', 'A body made up of nothing but muscle makes\nthe grappling moves this Pokémon performs with\nits tentacles tremendously powerful.', 80, 118, 90, 70, 80, 42, 8, 'Clobbopus, Grapploct'),
(854, '854', 'Sinistea', 'Ghost', 'https://example.com/images/types/ghost.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/sinistea.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/sinistea.mp3', 'This Pokémon is said to have been born when\na lonely spirit possessed a cold, leftover cup\nof tea.', 40, 45, 45, 74, 54, 50, 8, 'Sinistea, Polteageist'),
(855, '855', 'Polteageist', 'Ghost', 'https://example.com/images/types/ghost.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/polteageist.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/polteageist.mp3', 'This species lives in antique teapots.\nMost pots are forgeries, but on rare occasions,\nan authentic work is found.', 60, 65, 65, 134, 114, 70, 8, 'Sinistea, Polteageist'),
(856, '856', 'Hatenna', 'Psychic', 'https://example.com/images/types/psychic.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/hatenna.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/hatenna.mp3', 'Via the protrusion on its head, it senses other\ncreatures’ emotions. If you don’t have a calm\ndisposition, it will never warm up to you.', 42, 30, 45, 56, 53, 39, 8, 'Hatenna, Hattrem, Hatterene'),
(857, '857', 'Hattrem', 'Psychic', 'https://example.com/images/types/psychic.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/hattrem.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/hattrem.mp3', 'No matter who you are, if you bring strong\nemotions near this Pokémon, it will silence\nyou violently.', 57, 40, 65, 86, 73, 49, 8, 'Hatenna, Hattrem, Hatterene'),
(858, '858', 'Hatterene', 'Psychic, Fairy', 'https://example.com/images/types/psychic.png, https://example.com/images/types/fairy.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/hatterene.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/hatterene.mp3', 'It emits psychic power strong enough to cause\nheadaches as a deterrent to the approach\nof others.', 57, 90, 95, 136, 103, 29, 8, 'Hatenna, Hattrem, Hatterene'),
(859, '859', 'Impidimp', 'Dark, Fairy', 'https://example.com/images/types/dark.png, https://example.com/images/types/fairy.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/impidimp.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/impidimp.mp3', 'Through its nose, it sucks in the emanations\nproduced by people and Pokémon when they\nfeel annoyed. It thrives off this negative energy.', 45, 45, 30, 55, 40, 50, 8, 'Impidimp, Morgrem, Grimmsnarl'),
(860, '860', 'Morgrem', 'Dark, Fairy', 'https://example.com/images/types/dark.png, https://example.com/images/types/fairy.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/morgrem.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/morgrem.mp3', 'When it gets down on all fours as if to beg for\nforgiveness, it’s trying to lure opponents in so\nthat it can stab them with its spear-like hair.', 65, 60, 45, 75, 55, 70, 8, 'Impidimp, Morgrem, Grimmsnarl'),
(861, '861', 'Grimmsnarl', 'Dark, Fairy', 'https://example.com/images/types/dark.png, https://example.com/images/types/fairy.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/grimmsnarl.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/grimmsnarl.mp3', 'With the hair wrapped around its body helping to\nenhance its muscles, this Pokémon can overwhelm\neven Machamp.', 95, 120, 65, 95, 75, 60, 8, 'Impidimp, Morgrem, Grimmsnarl'),
(862, '862', 'Obstagoon', 'Dark, Normal', 'https://example.com/images/types/dark.png, https://example.com/images/types/normal.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/obstagoon.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/obstagoon.mp3', 'Its voice is staggering in volume. Obstagoon\nhas a tendency to take on a threatening posture\nand shout—this move is known as Obstruct.', 93, 90, 101, 60, 81, 95, 8, 'Zigzagoon, Linoone, Obstagoon'),
(863, '863', 'Perrserker', 'Steel', 'https://example.com/images/types/steel.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/perrserker.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/perrserker.mp3', 'What appears to be an iron helmet is actually\nhardened hair. This Pokémon lives for the thrill\nof battle.', 70, 110, 100, 50, 60, 50, 8, 'Meowth, Persian'),
(864, '864', 'Cursola', 'Ghost', 'https://example.com/images/types/ghost.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/cursola.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/cursola.mp3', 'Its shell is overflowing with its heightened\notherworldly energy. The ectoplasm serves as\nprotection for this Pokémon’s core spirit.', 60, 95, 50, 145, 130, 30, 8, 'Corsola, Cursola'),
(865, '865', 'Sirfetchd', 'Fighting', 'https://example.com/images/types/fighting.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/sirfetchd.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/sirfetchd.mp3', 'Only Farfetch’d that have survived many battles\ncan attain this evolution. When this Pokémon’s\nleek withers, it will retire from combat.', 62, 135, 95, 68, 82, 65, 8, 'Farfetchd, Sirfetchd'),
(866, '866', 'Mrrime', 'Ice, Psychic', 'https://example.com/images/types/ice.png, https://example.com/images/types/psychic.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/mrrime.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/mrrime.mp3', 'It’s highly skilled at tap-dancing. It waves its cane\nof ice in time with its graceful movements.', 80, 85, 75, 110, 100, 70, 8, 'Mime-jr, Mr-mime, Mr-rime'),
(867, '867', 'Runerigus', 'Ground, Ghost', 'https://example.com/images/types/ground.png, https://example.com/images/types/ghost.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/runerigus.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/runerigus.mp3', 'A powerful curse was woven into an ancient\npainting. After absorbing the spirit of a Yamask,\nthe painting began to move.', 58, 95, 145, 50, 105, 30, 8, 'Yamask, Cofagrigus'),
(868, '868', 'Milcery', 'Fairy', 'https://example.com/images/types/fairy.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/milcery.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/milcery.mp3', 'This Pokémon was born from sweet-smelling\nparticles in the air. Its body is made of cream.', 45, 40, 40, 50, 61, 34, 8, 'Milcery, Alcremie'),
(869, '869', 'Alcremie', 'Fairy', 'https://example.com/images/types/fairy.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/alcremie.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/alcremie.mp3', 'When it trusts a Trainer, it will treat them to\nberries it’s decorated with cream.', 65, 60, 75, 110, 121, 64, 8, 'Milcery, Alcremie'),
(870, '870', 'Falinks', 'Fighting', 'https://example.com/images/types/fighting.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/falinks.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/falinks.mp3', 'Five of them are troopers, and one is the brass.\nThe brass’s orders are absolute.', 65, 100, 100, 70, 60, 75, 8, 'Falinks'),
(871, '871', 'Pincurchin', 'Electric', 'https://example.com/images/types/electric.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/pincurchin.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/pincurchin.mp3', 'It feeds on seaweed, using its teeth to scrape it\noff rocks. Electric current flows from the tips of\nits spines.', 48, 101, 95, 91, 85, 15, 8, 'Pincurchin'),
(872, '872', 'Snom', 'Ice, Bug', 'https://example.com/images/types/ice.png, https://example.com/images/types/bug.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/snom.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/snom.mp3', 'It spits out thread imbued with a frigid sort of\nenergy and uses it to tie its body to branches,\ndisguising itself as an icicle while it sleeps.', 30, 25, 35, 45, 30, 20, 8, 'Snom, Frosmoth'),
(873, '873', 'Frosmoth', 'Ice, Bug', 'https://example.com/images/types/ice.png, https://example.com/images/types/bug.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/frosmoth.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/frosmoth.mp3', 'Icy scales fall from its wings like snow as it flies\nover fields and mountains. The temperature of its\nwings is less than −290 degrees Fahrenheit.', 70, 65, 60, 125, 90, 65, 8, 'Snom, Frosmoth'),
(874, '874', 'Stonjourner', 'Rock', 'https://example.com/images/types/rock.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/stonjourner.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/stonjourner.mp3', 'It stands in grasslands, watching the sun’s descent\nfrom zenith to horizon. This Pokémon has a talent\nfor delivering dynamic kicks.', 100, 125, 135, 20, 20, 70, 8, 'Stonjourner');
INSERT INTO `pokemon` (`id`, `pokedexNumber`, `name`, `type`, `type_images`, `image`, `cri`, `description`, `hp`, `attack`, `defense`, `special_attack`, `special_defense`, `speed`, `gen`, `evolution_chain`) VALUES
(875, '875', 'Eiscueice', 'Ice', 'https://example.com/images/types/ice.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/eiscueice.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/eiscueice.mp3', 'It drifted in on the flow of ocean waters from a\nfrigid place. It keeps its head iced constantly to\nmake sure it stays nice and cold.', 75, 80, 110, 65, 90, 50, 8, 'Eiscue'),
(876, '876', 'Indeedeemale', 'Psychic, Normal', 'https://example.com/images/types/psychic.png, https://example.com/images/types/normal.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/indeedeemale.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/indeedeemale.mp3', 'It uses the horns on its head to sense the\nemotions of others. Males will act as valets for\nthose they serve, looking after their every need.', 60, 65, 55, 105, 95, 95, 8, 'Indeedee'),
(877, '877', 'Morpekofullbelly', 'Electric, Dark', 'https://example.com/images/types/electric.png, https://example.com/images/types/dark.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/morpekofullbelly.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/morpekofullbelly.mp3', 'As it eats the seeds stored up in its pocket-like\npouches, this Pokémon is not just satisfying its\nconstant hunger. It’s also generating electricity.', 58, 95, 58, 70, 58, 97, 8, 'Morpeko'),
(878, '878', 'Cufant', 'Steel', 'https://example.com/images/types/steel.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/cufant.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/cufant.mp3', 'It digs up the ground with its trunk. It’s also very\nstrong, being able to carry loads of over\nfive tons without any problem at all.', 72, 80, 49, 40, 49, 40, 8, 'Cufant, Copperajah'),
(879, '879', 'Copperajah', 'Steel', 'https://example.com/images/types/steel.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/copperajah.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/copperajah.mp3', 'They came over from another region long\nago and worked together with humans.\nTheir green skin is resistant to water.', 122, 130, 69, 80, 69, 30, 8, 'Cufant, Copperajah'),
(880, '880', 'Dracozolt', 'Electric, Dragon', 'https://example.com/images/types/electric.png, https://example.com/images/types/dragon.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/dracozolt.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/dracozolt.mp3', 'In ancient times, it was unbeatable thanks to its\npowerful lower body, but it went extinct anyway\nafter it depleted all its plant-based food sources.', 90, 100, 90, 80, 70, 75, 8, 'Dracozolt'),
(881, '881', 'Arctozolt', 'Electric, Ice', 'https://example.com/images/types/electric.png, https://example.com/images/types/ice.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/arctozolt.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/arctozolt.mp3', 'The shaking of its freezing upper half is what\ngenerates its electricity. It has a hard time\nwalking around.', 90, 100, 90, 90, 80, 55, 8, 'Arctozolt'),
(882, '882', 'Dracovish', 'Water, Dragon', 'https://example.com/images/types/water.png, https://example.com/images/types/dragon.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/dracovish.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/dracovish.mp3', 'Powerful legs and jaws made it the apex predator\nof its time. Its own overhunting of its prey was\nwhat drove it to extinction.', 90, 90, 100, 70, 80, 75, 8, 'Dracovish'),
(883, '883', 'Arctovish', 'Water, Ice', 'https://example.com/images/types/water.png, https://example.com/images/types/ice.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/arctovish.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/arctovish.mp3', 'Though it’s able to capture prey by freezing its\nsurroundings, it has trouble eating the prey\nafterward because its mouth is on top of its head.', 90, 90, 100, 80, 90, 55, 8, 'Arctovish'),
(884, '884', 'Duraludon', 'Steel, Dragon', 'https://example.com/images/types/steel.png, https://example.com/images/types/dragon.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/duraludon.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/duraludon.mp3', 'Its body resembles polished metal, and it’s both\nlightweight and strong. The only drawback is that\nit rusts easily.', 70, 95, 115, 120, 50, 85, 8, 'Duraludon, Archaludon'),
(885, '885', 'Dreepy', 'Dragon, Ghost', 'https://example.com/images/types/dragon.png, https://example.com/images/types/ghost.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/dreepy.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/dreepy.mp3', 'After being reborn as a ghost Pokémon,\nDreepy wanders the areas it used to inhabit\nback when it was alive in prehistoric seas.', 28, 60, 30, 40, 30, 82, 8, 'Dreepy, Drakloak, Dragapult'),
(886, '886', 'Drakloak', 'Dragon, Ghost', 'https://example.com/images/types/dragon.png, https://example.com/images/types/ghost.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/drakloak.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/drakloak.mp3', 'It’s capable of flying faster than 120 mph.\nIt battles alongside Dreepy and\ndotes on them until they successfully evolve.', 68, 80, 50, 60, 50, 102, 8, 'Dreepy, Drakloak, Dragapult'),
(887, '887', 'Dragapult', 'Dragon, Ghost', 'https://example.com/images/types/dragon.png, https://example.com/images/types/ghost.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/sprites/bw/dragapult.png', 'https://play.pokemonshowdown.com/audio/cries/dragapult.mp3', 'When it isn’t battling, it keeps Dreepy in the\nholes on its horns. Once a fight starts, it launches\nthe Dreepy like supersonic missiles.', 88, 120, 75, 100, 75, 142, 8, 'Dreepy, Drakloak, Dragapult'),
